    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Knives of various designs to be used by coopers, saddlers, curriers, and other professions for making or fitting a head for an object. An example is the knife used by coopers to smooth and trim barrel heads to the proper angle to fit into the staves.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
